.vvn-bda.de/texte/0672_maria.htm] ]</ref> (born [[1910 in Germany|1910]])\n* 18 August \u2013 [[Sepp Daxenberger]], 48, German politician, [[bone marrow cancer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.br.de/error/brde-error4xx.html|title=Seite nicht gefunden [Fehler 404]: BR.de - der Bayerische Rundfunk im Internet|first=Bayerischer|last=Rundfunk|date=January 3, 2018|website=www.br.de}}</ref> (born [[1962 in Germany|1962]])\n* 19 August \u2013 [[Gerhard Beil]], 84, [[German Democratic Republic|East German]] politician.<ref>[http://www.edition-ost.de/aktuell-2/239-letzter-aussenhandelsminister-der-ddr-gerhard-beil-verstorben.html]{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> (born [[1926 in Germany|1926]])\n* 21 August \u2013 [[Christoph Schlingensief]], 49, German film and theatre director, lung cancer.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/08/25/arts/25schlingensief.html|title=Christoph Schlingensief, Artistic Provocateur, Dies at 49|first=William|last=Grimes|date=August 25, 2010|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> (born [[1960 in Germany|1960]])\n* 26 August \u2013 [[Walter Wolfrum]], 87, German [[World War II]] [[Luftwaffe]] [[fighter ace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://forum.12oclockhigh.net/showthread.php?p=112661|title=Walter Wolfrum - Luftwaffe and Allied Air Forces Discussion Forum|website=forum.12oclockhigh.net}}</ref> (born [[1923 in Germany|1923]])\n* 7 September \u2013 [[Eberhard von Brauchitsch]], 83, German industrial manager (born [[1926 in Germany|1926]])\n* 11 September \u2013 [[Baerbel Bohley]], 65, East German opposition figure & artist (born [[1945 in Germany|1945]])\n* 16 September \u2013 [[Friedrich Wilhelm, Prince of Hohenzollern]], 86, German nobleman (born [[1924 in Germany|1924]])\n* 18 September \u2013 [[Egon Klepsch]], 80, German politician (born [[1930 in Germany|1930]])\n* 14 October \u2013 [[Hermann Scheer]], 66, German politician (born [[1944 in Germany|1944]])\n* 21 October \u2013 [[Loki Schmidt]], 91, German [[Environmental movement|environmentalist]] and wife of [[Helmut Schmidt]]. (born [[1919 in Germany|1919]])\n* 5 November \u2013 [[Hajo Herrmann]], 97, German [[Luftwaffe]] pilot (born [[1913 in Germany|1913]])\n* 6 November \u2013 [[Ezard Hau\u00dfmann]], 75, German actor (born [[1935 in Germany|1935]])\n* 15 November \u2013 [[Andreas Kirchner]], 57, German Winter sportsman (born [[1953 in Germany|1953]])\n* 20 November:\n** [[Walter Helmut Fritz]], German author (born [[1929 in Germany|1929]])\n** [[Heinz Weiss]], German actor (born [[1921 in Germany|1921]])\n* 26 November \u2013 [[Maria Hellwig]], 90, German singer (born [[1920 in Germany|1920]])\n* 30 November \u2013 [[Peter Hofmann]], 76, German singer (born [[1944 in Germany|1944]])\n* 7 December \u2013 [[Armin Weiss]], 83, chemist and politician (born [[1927 in Germany|1927]])\n* 7 December \u2013 [[Arnold Weiss]], 86, German-born American soldier (born [[1924 in Germany|1924]])\n* 15 December \u2013 [[Hans-Joachim Rauschenbach]], 87, German sport journalist (born [[1923 in Germany|1923]])\n* 17 December \u2013 [[Mikhail Umansky]], 58, Russian-born German chess grandmaster (born [[1952 in Russia|1952]])\n* 20 December - [[Katharina Szelinski-Singer]], 92, German sculptor (born [[1918 in Germany|1918]])\n\n==See also==\n*[[2010 in German television]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Germany at the 2010 Winter Olympics]]\n\n{{Germany year nav}}\n{{Year in Europe|2010}}\n\n[[Category:2010 in Germany| ]]\n[[Category:Years of the 21st century in Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{yearbox|\n in?= in Germany|\n cp=20th Century|\n c=21st century |\n cf=22nd century |\n\n yp1=2007 |\n yp2=2008 |\n yp3=2009 |\n year=2010 |\n ya1=2011 |\n ya2=2012 |\n ya3=2013 |\n dp3=1980s |\n dp2=1990s |\n dp1=2000s |\n d=2010\u20132019{{!}}2010s |\n da=0 |\n dn1=2020s |\n dn2=2030s |\n dn3=2040s |\n}}\nEvents in the year '''2010 in [[Germany]]'''.\n\n==Incumbents==\n\n===Federal level===\n* [[President of Germany|President]] \u2013\n** until 31 May: [[Horst K\u00f6hler]] \n** 31 May-30 June: [[Jens B\u00f6hrnsen]]\n** starting 30 June: [[Christian Wulff]]\n* [[Chancellor of Germany (Federal Republic)|Chancellor]] \u2013 [[Angela Merkel]]\n\n==Events==\n[[File:Lena Meyer-Landrut at PC after 2010 Eurovision 2.jpg|thumb|right|150px|Germany's [[Lena Meyer-Landrut|Lena]] wins the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2010]]]]\n* 16 January \u2013 The German government asks its citizens to stop using [[Microsoft]]'s [[web browser]] [[Internet Explorer]] to protect their own security.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/technology/8463516.stm|title=Germany issues Explorer warning|date=January 16, 2010|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>\n* 22 January \u2013 A [[Nuremberg]] court issues an [[arrest warrant]] for former [[Argentina|Argentine]] leader [[Jorge Rafael Videla]], on suspicion of killing a German man.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/americas/8476321.stm|title=Germany seeks Argentina's Videla|date=January 22, 2010|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/germany-seeks-arrest-of-former-argentine-dictator/a-5161476|title=Germany seeks arrest of former Argentine dictator|website=Deutsche Welle |date=22 January 2010}}</ref>\n* 11\u201321 February \u2013 [[60th Berlin International Film Festival]]\n* 13 February \u2013 More than 10,000 [[2010 Dresden anti-fascist blockade|anti-fascist protesters]] successfully block a planned [[Neo-Nazism|neo-Nazi]] march in [[Dresden]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Becker |first1=Leon Dische |title=Dresden's 'Civil Courage': A City Mobilizes Against Neo-Nazis |url=https://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/dresden-s-civil-courage-a-city-mobilizes-against-neo-nazis-a-678069.html |accessdate=2019-11-18 |work=[[Spiegel Online]] |date=15 February 2010}}</ref>\n* 4 April \u2013 Three [[4 April 2010 Baghdad bombings|car bombs hit]] the Egyptian, German and Iranian embassies in the centre of the Iraqi capital, [[Baghdad]], in quick succession, killing at least 30 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/middle_east/8602478.stm |title=Iraqi capital rocked by bombs leaving 41 dead |work=[[BBC News]] |date=2010-04-04 |accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref>\n* 29 May \u2013 With the song \"[[Satellite (Lena Meyer-Landrut song)|Satellite]]\", Germany's [[Lena Meyer-Landrut|Lena]] wins the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2010]], the first German victory since [[Eurovision Song Contest 1982|1982]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fulker |first1=Rick |title=S!sters to enter the fray as Germany's Eurovision candidate in Tel Aviv |url=https://www.dw.com/en/ssters-to-enter-the-fray-as-germanys-eurovision-candidate-in-tel-aviv/a-47644877 |accessdate=12 November 2019 |work=Deutsche Welle |date=22 February 2019}}</ref>\n* 25 June \u2013 Germany's [[TanDEM-X]] satellite, whose aim it is to create the most precise [[Three-dimensional space|3D]] map of [[Earth]]'s surface, obtains its first images.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/10422511|title=3D mission returns first pictures|first=Jonathan|last=Amos|date=June 26, 2010|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>\n* 30 June \u2014 [[Christian Wulff]] is elected [[President of Germany]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Connolly |first1=Kate |title=Christian Wulff elected German president |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/jun/30/christian-wulff-elected-german-president |accessdate=2019-11-18 |work=The Guardian |date=30 June 2010}}</ref>\n* 4 July \u2013 In a referendum, voters in the [[States of Germany|German state]] of [[Bavaria]] vote to ban smoking at all pubs and restaurants.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/munich-beer-fest-votes-to-ban-smoking-20100705-zw3b.html|title=Munich beer fest votes to ban smoking|date=July 4, 2010|website=The Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref>\n* 7 July \u2013 [[Spain national football team|Spain]] defeats [[Germany national football team|Germany]] 1-0 to win its [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|semi-final]] and for its first time, along with [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] make the [[2010 FIFA World Cup Final]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=McCarra |first1=Kevin |title=Germany 0-1 Spain {{!}} World Cup 2010 semi-final match report |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/jul/07/germany-spain-world-cup-match-report |accessdate=12 November 2019 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=7 July 2010}}</ref>\n* 10 July \u2013 [[2010 FIFA World Cup]]: [[Germany national football team|Germany]] defeats [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] 3-2 to finish [[2010 FIFA World Cup knockout stage|third]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2010/matches/match_63/default.stm|first=David |last=Ornstein|title=Uruguay 2-3 Germany|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>\n* 12 July \u2013 At least eight people are injured after a tornado strikes the German island of [[Duene]] in the [[North Sea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/10606081|title=Eight injured in German tornado|date=July 12, 2010|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>\n* 24 July \u2013 [[Love Parade stampede|A massive stampede at the 2010 Love Parade in Duisburg]] kills 20 people and injures dozens more people.\n* 8 August  \u2013 Dutch rider [[Ellen van Dijk]] wins the [[2010 Sparkassen Giro]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Wielerzege voor Van Dijk in Duitsland |url=https://www.nu.nl/wielrennen/2308380/wielerzege-van-dijk-in-duitsland.html |accessdate=2019-11-18 |work=[[NU.nl]] |date=8 August 2010 |language=nl}}</ref>\n* 26 August \u2013 German [[HIV-positive]] pop singer [[Nadja Benaissa]] is found guilty of [[grievous bodily harm]] after transmitting HIV to a man who had [[unprotected sex]] with her without her telling him of her condition.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Connolly |first1=Kate |title=German singer Nadja Benaissa sentenced for infecting lover with HIV |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/aug/26/nadja-benaissa-hiv-sentence-germany |accessdate=2019-11-18 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=26 August 2010}}</ref>\n* 21\u201326 September \u2013 [[photokina 2010|photokina]] in Cologne\n* 28 September \u2013 Germany's \u00a322 billion [[World War I]] debt is finally paid off after more than 90 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-1315869/Germany-end-World-War-One-reparations-92-years-59m-final-payment.html|title=Germany finally ends World War One reparations after 92 years with \u00a359m final payment to France|date=September 28, 2010|website=Mail Online}}</ref>\n* 3 October \u2013 \n** Germany celebrates 20 years of [[Unification of Germany|unification]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-11461199|title=Germany marks 20 years of unity|date=October 3, 2010|work=[[BBC News]]}}</ref> \n** The German government pays its last [[World War I reparations]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Crossland |first1=David |title=Germany to Settle WWI Debt After 92 Years |url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/germany-makes-final-reparation-payments-world-war/story?id=11755920 |accessdate=12 November 2019 |work=ABC News |date=29 September 2010 }}</ref>\n* 26 October \u2013 The number of unemployed in Germany drops first time since 1991 below three million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/number-of-german-jobless-hits-18-year-low/a-6158584|title=Number of German jobless hits 18-year low |date=27 October 2010|work=Deutsche Welle}}</ref>\n* 1 November \u2013 [[German identity card]]s are issued in the ISO/IEC 7810 ID-1 format and contain RFID chips with [[personally identifiable information]] including a biometric Photo and, if desired, two fingerprints.\n[[File:WendlandAntiNuclearProtest9.jpg|thumb|200px|Anti-Atomkraft-Demonstration in Wendland (2010)]]\n[[File:Freya von Moltke 2009.jpg|thumb|180px|right|[[Freya von Moltke]]<br>Photo: Dorothea von Haeften]]\n[[File:Bundesarchiv B 145 Bild-F054635-0016, Ludwigshafen, CDU-Bundesparteitag, Laurien.jpg|thumb|180px|right|[[Hanna-Renate Laurien]]]]\n[[File:Werner Schroeter.jpg|thumb|180px|right|[[Werner Schroeter]]]]\n[[File:Heidi Kabel Portrait.jpg|thumb|180px|right|[[Heidi Kabel]]]]\n[[File:SeppDaxenberger1086.jpg|thumb|180px|right|[[Sepp Daxenberger]]]]\n[[File:Bundesarchiv B 145 Bild-F061601-0016, Bundeswehrkrankenhaus Koblenz, Schmidt mit Gattin cropped.jpg|thumb|180px|right|[[Loki Schmidt]]]]\n* 9 November \u2013 Demonstrations in [[L\u00fcchow-Dannenberg|Wendland]] near [[Gorleben]] against [[CASTOR (nuclear waste)|CASTOR]]-transport.<ref>{{cite news |title=Wendland: Zehntausende protestieren gegen Castor-Transport |url=https://www.welt.de/politik/deutschland/article10770590/Zehntausende-protestieren-gegen-Castor-Transport.html |accessdate=2019-11-18 |work=[[Welt (German TV channel)|Welt]] |date=6 November 2010}}</ref>\n* 29 November \u2013 Break of coalition in [[Hamburg]] between the [[Green party|Green]] and [[Christian Democratic Union (Germany)|CDU]] parties.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.spiegel.de/politik/deutschland/hamburg-gal-beendet-schwarz-gruene-koalition-a-731577.html|title=Hamburg: GAL beendet schwarz-gr\u00fcne Koalition|date=November 28, 2010|work=[[Spiegel Online]] |language=de}}</ref>\n* December \u2013 The German Meteorological Service, {{lang|de|[[Deutscher Wetterdienst|Deutsche Wetterdienst]]}}, says December was the coldest December month since 1969 in Germany.<ref>{{cite web |title=State of the Climate: Global Climate Report for December 2010 |url=https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/sotc/global/201012 |website=NOAA National Centers for Environmental Information |accessdate=2019-11-18 |date=January 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Deaths ==\n* 1 January \u2013 [[Marlene Neubauer-Woerner]], 91, German sculptor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pnp.de/archiv/cho/728501_Floetenspieler-Schoepferin-gestorben.html|title=Fl\u00f6tenspieler-Sch\u00f6pferin gestorben |date=5 January 2010 |author=<!-- no byline -->|work=[[Passauer Neue Presse]] |accessdate=2019-11-10 |language=de}}</ref> (born [[1918 in Germany|1918]])\n* 1 January \u2013 [[Freya von Moltke]], 98, German [[World War II]] [[resistance fighter]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/6937604/Freya-von-Moltke.html|title=Freya von Moltke|date=January 5, 2010|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=2019-11-10}}</ref> (born [[1911 in Germany|1911]])\n* 4 January \u2013 [[Ludwig Wilding]], 82, German artist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.augsburger-allgemeine.de/Home/Lokales/Neuburg/Lokalnachrichten/Artikel,-Ludwig-Wilding-ist-tot-_arid,2040891_regid,2_puid,2_pageid,4502.html |title=Nachrichten Neuburg |work=[[Augsburger Allgemeine]] |language=de |date= |accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref> (born [[1927 in Germany|1927]])\n* 9 January \u2013 [[Franz-Hermann Br\u00fcner]], 64, German head of [[European Anti-fraud Office|OLAF]], after long illness.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politico.eu/article/head-of-olaf-dies/|title=Head of OLAF dies|first=European|last=Voice|date=January 11, 2010|website=POLITICO}}</ref> (born [[1945 in Germany|1945]])\n* 9 January \u2013 [[Diether Posser]], 87, German politician.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.derwesten.de/incoming/ehemaliger-spd-finanzminister-diether-posser-gestorben-id2374313.html|title=Ehemaliger SPD-Finanzminister Diether Posser gestorben|first=Matthias|last=Korfmann|date=January 11, 2010|website=Der Westen |trans-title=Former SPD finance minister Diether Posser dies |language=de}}</ref> (born [[1922 in Germany|1922]])\n* 14 January \u2013 [[Katharina Rutschky]], 68, German [[educationalist]] and author.<ref>{{cite web|author=Dirk Knipphals |url=http://www.taz.de/1/leben/koepfe/artikel/1/die-urbane-intellektuelle/ |title=Nachruf Katharina Rutschky: Ironisch, intellektuell und lebensfroh |publisher=taz.de |date=2011-04-08 |accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref> (born [[1941 in Germany|1941]])\n* 14 January \u2013 [[Petra Sch\u00fcrmann]], 74, German television presenter, [[Miss World 1956]], after long illness.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.merkur.de/boulevard/tv-moderatorin-petra-schuermann-591118.html|title=TV-Moderatorin Petra Sch\u00fcrmann ist tot: Sie wollte ihre Tochter im Himmel wiedersehen|date=January 14, 2010|newspaper=M\u00fcnchner Merkur}}</ref> (born [[1933 in Germany|1933]])\n* 15 January \u2013 [[Detlev Lauscher]], 57, German [[association football|footballer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bazonline.ch/|title=Basler Zeitung - Aktuelle Nachrichten aus Basel|via=www.bazonline.ch}}</ref> (born [[1952 in Germany|1952]])\n* 18 January \u2013 [[G\u00fcnter Mielke]], 67, German Olympic athlete.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.germanroadraces.de/24-0-14215-guenter-mielke-ist-tot.html |title=G\u00fcnter Mielke ist tot |access-date=2 September 2010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719032157/http://www.germanroadraces.de/24-0-14215-guenter-mielke-ist-tot.html |archive-date=19 July 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all |website=German Road Races |language=de |trans-title=G\u00fcnter Mielke is dead }}</ref> (born [[1942 in Germany|1942]])\n* 30 January \u2013 [[Ruth Cohn]], 97, German [[psychotherapy|psychotherapist]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www1.wdr.de/radio/index.html?datum=2010-1-31&tag=31&monat=1&jahr=2010&seite=4&block=2|title=WDR Radio h\u00f6ren - Alle Sender des Westdeutschen Rundfunks im Livestream - Radio - WDR|date=June 17, 2019|website=www1.wdr.de}}</ref> (born [[1912 in Germany|1912]])\n* 31 January \u2013 [[Erna Baumbauer]], 91, German [[talent agent|casting agent]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roxborough |first1=Scott |title=Casting agent Erna Baumbauer dies |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/casting-agent-erna-baumbauer-dies-20200 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=10 November 2019 |date=2 February 2010}}</ref> (born [[1919 in Germany|1919]])\n* 10 February \u2013 [[Michael Palme]], 66, German [[sportswriter]] and [[Host (radio)|host]].<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.faz.net/|title=Aktuelle Nachrichten online|first=Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung|l