rman [[association football|footballer]] ([[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]), throat cancer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224024724/http://www.thebluenose.co.uk/news/assembly-news/gerry-dies-after-brave-fight-20100224361/ |title=thebluenose.co.uk |publisher=Web.archive.org |date= |accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref> (born [[1946 in Germany|1946]])\n* 23 February \u2013 [[Henri Salmide]], 90, German [[World War II]] [[naval officer]], saved [[Bordeaux]] port from destruction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archive.boston.com/bostonglobe/obituaries/articles/2010/02/27/henri_salmide_his_defiance_saved_port_of_bordeaux_from_nazis/|title=Henri Salmide; his defiance saved port of Bordeaux from Nazis|date=February 27, 2010|via=The Boston Globe}}</ref> (born [[1919 in Germany|1919]])\n* 27 February \u2013 [[David Bankier]], 63, German-born Israeli [[Holocaust]] scholar.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/03/01/world/middleeast/01bankier.html|title=David Bankier, Scholar of Holocaust, Dies at 63|first=Ethan|last=Bronner|date=February 28, 2010|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> (born [[1947 in Germany|1947]])\n* 5 March \u2013 [[Wolfgang Schenck (pilot)|Wolfgang Schenck]], 97, German airman, [[Luftwaffe]] [[flying ace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://accounts.google.com/ServiceLogin?service=blogger&hl=en-US&passive=true&continue=https://www.blogger.com/blogin.g?blogspotURL%3Dhttp://saladeguerra.blogspot.com/2010/03/nota-de-falecimento-wolfgang-schenck.html%26zx%3D1cdaq5duxbuz7|title=Blogger|website=accounts.google.com}}</ref> (born [[1913 in Namibia|1913]])\n* 12 March \u2013 [[Hanna-Renate Laurien]], 81, German politician.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.spiegel.de/politik/deutschland/trauer-in-berlin-cdu-politikerin-laurien-ist-tot-a-683346.html|title=Trauer in Berlin: CDU-Politikerin Laurien ist tot|date=March 12, 2010|via=Spiegel Online}}</ref> (born [[1928 in Germany|1928]])\n* 14 March \u2013 [[Konrad Ruhland]], 78, German [[musicology|musicologist]].<ref>