ektrische Viktoria|Siemens]]), car crash.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.badische-zeitung.de/titisee-neustadt/siemens-projektleiter-stirbt-bei-fahrt-mit-elektro-oldtimer|title=Siemens-Projektleiter stirbt bei Fahrt mit Elektro-Oldtimer - Titisee-Neustadt - Badische Zeitung|first=Badische|last=Zeitung|website=www.badische-zeitung.de}}</ref> (born [[1947 in Germany|1947]])\n* 22 June \u2013 [[Marie-Luise Jahn]], 92, German activist, member of the anti-Nazi resistance movement [[White Rose]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/muenchen/dachau/vermischtes/zeitzeugin-der-weissen-rose-marie-luise-schultze-jahn-ist-tot-1.964482 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100628162642/http://www.sueddeutsche.de/muenchen/dachau/vermischtes/zeitzeugin-der-weissen-rose-marie-luise-schultze-jahn-ist-tot-1.964482 |archive-date=2010-06-28 |title=Zeitzeugin der \"Wei\u00dfen Rose\" - Marie-Luise Schultze-Jahn ist tot |newspaper=Sueddeutsche Zeitung |date= |accessdate=2019-07-03}}</ref> (born [[1918 in Germany|1918]])\n* 22 June \u2013 [[Manfred R\u00f6mbell]], 68, German writer, after long illness.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.volksfreund.de/region/kultur/saarlaendischer-autor-manfred-roembell-ist-tot_aid-5980422|title=Saarl\u00e4ndischer Autor Manfred R\u00f6mbell ist tot|website=Volksfreund}}</ref> (born [[1941 in Germany|1941]])\n* 23 June \u2013 [[J\u00f6rg Berger]], 65, German [[Manager (association football)|football manager]], [[colorectal cancer|bowel cancer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.supersport.com/football/germany/news/100624/Former_Bundesliga_coach_Berger_dies|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721054723/http://www.supersport.com/football/germany/news/100624/Former_Bundesliga_coach_Berger_dies|archivedate=2011-07-21|title=Former Bundesliga coach Berger dies - SuperSport - Football|date=July 21, 2011|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> (born [[1944 in Germany|1944]])\n* 23 June \u2013 [[Frank Giering]], 38, German actor (''[[Funny Games (1997 fil