{"title_page": "Faith Ng", "text_new": "{{Underlinked|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Playwright (b. 1987)}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name = Faith Ng\n| birth_date = {{Birth date|year=1987|month=6|day=25|mf=yes}}\n| occupation = Playwright\n| language = English\n| nationality = Singapore\n}}'''Faith Ng''' (born 25 June 1987) is a Singaporean playwright. Her plays are noted for their rich characterization and sensitive portrayals of Singapore life.<ref name = \"Said 2018\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/theatre-review-normal-is-a-sensitive-portrayal-of-the-challenges-of-school|title=Theatre review: Normal is a sensitive portrayal of the challenges of school life|last=Said|first=Nabilah|date=2015-04-10|work=The Straits Times|access-date=2018-12-01|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181201180809/https://www.straitstimes.com/lifestyle/entertainment/theatre-review-normal-is-a-sensitive-portrayal-of-the-challenges-of-school|archive-date=2018-12-01|url-status=live}}</ref> She is currently the Associate Artistic Director of Checkpoint Theatre.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://checkpoint-theatre.org/about-ct/team?tab=about-faith|title=About Team {{!}} Checkpoint Theatre|website=checkpoint-theatre.org|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181201135453/https://checkpoint-theatre.org/about-ct/team?tab=about-faith|archive-date=2018-12-01|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nNg is the second daughter of Stefanie, a tutor, and Raymond, a logistics manager.<ref name = \"Said 2018\" /> She has a twin sister named Debbie; their elder sister is Cheryl. She is married to theatre academic Assistant Professor Alvin Lim.\n\n== Works ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Stage\n!Year\n!Title\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n|-\n|2010\n|''wo(men)''\n|A NUS Arts Festival 2010 commission & Festival Opening Production<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://checkpoint-theatre.org/past-productions/women|title=wo(men) {{!}}